parameters: Yo! Can't start without weapons, right?! So come on, buy 'em up!

Yo! First, let's strengthen your armor! Buy lots and lots from
me!

That shopkeeper is competing in sales, you know. But I think the
demand for weapons and armor is different.

B Knight Doream: This full-body armor... What a magnificent
masterpiece...! It's amazing...! It's too heavy for me to equip,
though...

Hmm... Should I buy armor to reduce damage or buy a weapon to
finish things off quickly... I don't know the right answer.
被弾役と攻撃役を分担！

There's only one correct answer, right? I'm not very reliable
with my moderate strength though...

There's no doubt about it, right? I can't use magic that can
create situations though...
被弾役と攻撃役を分担！

There's no way I have friends who would take the attacks for
me...! I've been fooled! How awful! You!!

...If you have friends like that, you should cherish them,
shouldn't you?
Miko with a focus on coordination

I want to wear a dress rather than heavy armor.... Ah, when I
wear cute clothes, I feel more motivated.

I don't know what to buy for weapons and armor! ...Do you ever
think that? If you want, shall I give you some advice?

Until you have all your equipment equipped, it's best to
prioritize armor. Once you have everything in place, then you can
prioritize weapons! First, aim for that!

I'll get into some serious talk, but even if your attack power is
low, you won't end up dealing 0 damage due to the calculation
formula. So don't worry, I (probably) won't make you feel
helpless like that.

In this game, defense power doesn't increase much. Instead,
maximum HP and maximum MP increase. So, well, use those as a
reference! That's all!!
